List is an ordered collection of elements. It allows duplicate elements and maintains the insertion order.
Key Properties
    - Maintains insertion order
    - Allows duplicates
    - Supports index-based access
    - Allows null elements

Common Implementations
    - ArrayList: is implemented using a dynamic array. It stores elements in an internal Object array.
    - LinkedList: Doubly-linked list implementation, provides better performance for insertions and deletions but slower random access compared to ArrayList.
    - Vector: Synchronized resizable array implementation


Arrays va ArrayLists :
----------------------
Arrays have fixed size and support primitive types,
while ArrayList has dynamic size and supports only objects but provides many built-in methods like add(), remove(), and contains() for easier manipulation of elements.
Disadvantage:
❌ Slow insertion/deletion in the middle

| Feature    | Array               | ArrayList             |
| ---------- | ------------------- | --------------------- |
| Size       | Fixed               | Dynamic               |
| Data Types | Primitive + Objects | Objects only          |
| Methods    | Limited             | Many built-in methods |


ArrayList vs LinkedList :
--------------------------

| Feature            | ArrayList                  | LinkedList                           |
| ------------------ | -------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Internal structure | Dynamic array              | Doubly linked list                   |
| Memory storage     | Continuous memory          | Nodes connected by references        |
| Access (get)       | **O(1)** fast              | **O(n)** slow                        |
| Insert at middle   | **O(n)** (shifting needed) | **O(1)** (change pointers)           |
| Delete at middle   | **O(n)**                   | **O(1)**                             |
| Memory usage       | Less (stores only data)    | More (stores prev & next references) |
| Best use case      | Frequent access            | Frequent insert/delete               |



